"Poured from a 22 oz bomber into 16 oz snifter. A: nice dark cola-like color with about an inch of tan head that disappears rather quickly with almost no lacing afterward. S: probably the best part of the beer in my opinion, deep chocolate and toasty goodness, almost reminds me of my sister's coffee drinks, alcohol is hidden very well in this one; my only complaint is the peanut butter is almost at the back end of the smell, you kind of have to search for it. T: very good flavor on this, peanut butter flavor is kind of masked on the flavor as well, hop bitters on the front of the tongue do this beer very well and with a sweet finish, it tastes very well balanced, I could definitely drink multiple beers without getting tired of this! M: feels nice and thin, but not watery, a very nice feel, even for a stout. Overall I would say this is an exceptional stout, I would definitely buy this again, maybe multiple bottles at a time."
